         <div class="mainpage" style="color:Blue">Our history</div>
         <p class="text">Teddy Books is one of the most sucessful book publisher in Malaysia as well as South East Asia. Teddy Books
    was founded on 1956 by Datuk Tuk Gajah Besar, a well known author in the Malay community. When asked why he named it Teddy Books,
    he answered: "My bookstore is as big as an Teddy! hahaha..". From a small bookstore in Kuala Lumpur, Datuk Tuk Gajah Besar managed 
    to open up more bookstore all our Selangor and soon, each state in Malaysia has at least one Teddy Books bookstore. <br /><br />
    
    In the year of 1983, Datuk Tuk Gajah Besar passed away and his son, Dr. Johnson Gajah take over his father throne. 
    With the experience of studying aboard, Dr. Johnson Gajah has the ambition to open up the first Teddy Books bookstore on foreign soil,
    which was located on Jakarta, Indonesia at the year of 1990.</p>
         

